INSERT INTO `Sports` VALUES (1,'India at CWG, day 6: Heena, men\'s hockey team, boxers lift medal count',NULL,'2018-04-10','Heena, 28, dominated her finals with a Games record total of 38.\nThis was the second medal of the Heena, 28, dominated her finals with a Games record total of 38.\nOverall, India’s shooting contingent have won eight medals in Australia.In the men’s 46-49kg boxing quarter-finals, Amit defeated Scotland’s Aqeel Ahmed 4-1 to advance.\nIndia opened their account as early as the third minute when Harmanpreet Singh found the net with his drag flick.\nIndia\'s midfield had a good day, constantly putting the Malaysian defence under pressure, but the forwards lacked the finishing touch.','https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/commonwealth-games/india-at-cwg-day-6-heena-mens-hockey-team-boxers-lift-medal-count/articleshow/63690262.cms','Commonwealth Games News: Gold medalist Heena Sidhu, the Indian men’s hockey team and boxers Amit Phangal, Naman Tanwar, Mohammed Hussamuddin and Manoj Kumar all made headlines','https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/msid-63690270,width-1070,height-580,imgsize-1221285,resizemode-6,overlay-toi_sw,pt-32,y_pad-40/photo.jpg','total'),(2,'India at CWG, day 6: Heena, men\'s hockey team, boxers lift medal count',NULL,'2018-04-10','Heena, 28, dominated her finals with a Games record total of 38.\nThis was the second medal of the Heena, 28, dominated her finals with a Games record total of 38.\nOverall, India’s shooting contingent have won eight medals in Australia.In the men’s 46-49kg boxing quarter-finals, Amit defeated Scotland’s Aqeel Ahmed 4-1 to advance.\nIndia opened their account as early as the third minute when Harmanpreet Singh found the net with his drag flick.\nIndia\'s midfield had a good day, constantly putting the Malaysian defence under pressure, but the forwards lacked the finishing touch.','https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/commonwealth-games/india-at-cwg-day-6-heena-mens-hockey-team-boxers-lift-medal-co